FAIL_TO_PASS: when unknown command and showSuggestionAfterError() then show suggestion
when command-argument is -123.45 then consumed=true
when specify unknown option with subcommand and action handler then error
when digit option defined and command-argument is -1.2e+3 then negative not consumed
when option-argument for short optional is -x-1 then consumed=false
when option-argument for short optional... is 1 then consumed=true
when passed string then treat as boolean
when shared option before sub and after sub and after sub parameter then all three parsed
when action handler for subcommand then emit command:subcommand
when required option-argument and default number then value is default
when has conflicting option then throw CommanderError
when default writeErr() then error on stderr
when digit option defined and option-argument is then negative not consumed
when source cli and env default then implied is env
when env defined and value source is config then option from env
when digit option defined and option-argument is -123 then negative not consumed
when enablePositionalOptions() then option parsed by subcommand
when "program help sub1" then sub1
when command-argument is -1.2e-3 then consumed=true
when program has mandatory-yes/mandatory-no flag specified with flag then true
